           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">As Instagram remains blocked in Turkey, Erdogan accuses social media companies of 'digital fascism'</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      ANKARA, Turkey (AP) — Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan accused social media platforms of “digital fascism” on Monday for allegedly censoring photographs of Palestinian “martyrs.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/05/as-instagram-remains-blocked-in-turkey-erdogan-accuses-social-media-companies-of-digital-fascism/"  >(Associated Press, NewsNation)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Thu, 01 Aug 2024 02:37:01 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Thu, 01 Aug 2024 02:37:01 +0000">
