    <h3 itemprop="headline">Valdez loses no-hitter with 2 outs in 9th on Seager homer as Astros beat rival Rangers 4-2</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) — Framber Valdez was so steady for eight innings. A wobbly ninth cost the Houston left-hander his second career no-hitter. Valdez was an out away from more history when Texas slugger Corey Seager hit a two-run homer in the Astros' 4-2 victory over the Rangers on Tuesday night.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/sports/2024/08/07/valdez-loses-no-hitter-with-2-outs-in-9th-on-seager-homer-as-astros-beat-rangers-4-2/"  >(SCHUYLER DIXON, Associated Press, PHL 17)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
